  "text": "The first approach requires close attention to changes in lifestyle, including diet and exercise. Gradual weight loss and exercise together have been demonstrated to improve ALT levels and liver histology in adults [47 ,48] . However, the rate and degree of weight loss required for normalization of liver histology have not yet been established for paediatric patients, and it has been shown that very rapid weight loss associated with a very low calorie diet can actually worsen the degree of liver inflammation in children with NASH [49 ,50] . Because of the association amongobesity,insulin resistance andNASH, weightreduction by bariatric surgery has also been proposed as potential treatment in obese adolescents with NASH, but such studies in paediatric patients are currently lacking [CITATION_1] .",
